https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500null The NET original production, "68: The Year Nebraska Mattered," is a close up view of the 1968 Presidential election and how Nebraska played a key role in shaping the outcome. The program features video from the era along with present-day interviews. It covers all of the main players like Richard Nixon, Robert Kennedy, Hubert Humphrey, Eugene McCarthy, Nelson Rockefeller and George Wallace. '68: The Year Nebraska Mattered
